Annotation

Conclusion and Recommendations based on this report and previous findings known to us
The patient shows mildly elevated serum creatinine, suggesting possible renal impairment. Urinalysis reveals proteinuria, glucosuria, bilirubinuria, low specific gravity, and abnormal urine appearance (cloudy, brown, ammoniacal), which may indicate renal dysfunction and possible hepatic involvement. No evidence of urinary tract infection is seen. Recommend further evaluation of renal and hepatic function and correlation with clinical findings.
